HEADWORD: Reclinate
<hw>Rec"li*nate</hw> <pr>(r⟦ecr⟧k"l⟦icr⟧*n⟦asl⟧t)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>reclinatus</ets>, p. p.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Reclined, as a leaf; bent downward, so that the point, as of a stem
or leaf, is lower than the base.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reclination</ent>⟦br⟧
